ue,"entry_ids":["n44568"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of وَاسِع (wāsiʕ):; wider; widest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of وَاسِع (wāsiʕ):; more spacious; most spacious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make wide, to broaden"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be rich; to become rich"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be profuse, to spread one’s copiosity","examples":[{"text":"إِذَا وَسَّعَ اللَّهُ فَأَوْسِعُوا، جَمَعَ رَجُلٌ عَلَيْهِ ثِيَابَهُ، صَلَّى رَجُلٌ فِي إِزَارٍ وَرِدَاءٍ، فِي إِزَارٍ وَقَمِيصٍ، فِي إِزَارٍ وَقَبَاءٍ، فِي سَرَاوِيلَ وَرِدَاءٍ، فِي سَرَاوِيلَ وَقَمِيصٍ، فِي سَرَاوِيلَ وَقَبَاءٍ، فِي تُبَّانٍ وَقَبَاءٍ، فِي تُبَّانٍ وَقَمِيصٍ ـ قَالَ وَأَحْسِبُهُ قَالَ ـ فِي تُبَّانٍ وَرِدَاءٍ.","english":"When Allah makes you wealthier then you should clothe yourself properly during prayers. Otherwise one can pray with an ʾizār and a ridaʾ, ʾizār and a shirt, ʾizār and a qabāʾ, trousers and a ridaʾ, trousers and a shirt or trousers and a qabāʾ, tubbān and a qabāʾ or tubbān and a shirt. (The narrator added, “I think that he also said a tubbān and a ridaʾ.”)"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go rough on, to wallop"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of وَاسِع (wāsiʕ, “wide; spacious”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44568","headword_ar":"اَوْسَعُ","root":"wsE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"widest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 3 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlT","text_ar":"خلط"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}